main event: A white circular or elliptical object was observed for 2 minutes over San Diego, California, on March 6, 1952.
interesting points: The object was seen traveling in level flight from west to east., It was positioned at an elevation of 12-15 degrees., The angular size of the object was approximately 6 arc degrees., Several witnesses reported the sighting, indicating a significant level of corroboration., The report concluded that there was insufficient data for further evaluation.
sighted object: one white circular or elliptical object
witness description: Multiple independent witnesses including an Air Force captain who sighted the object.
